author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Men's soccer | Holschuh's goal lifts Va. Wesleyan
text:
ROANOKE Robert Holschuh scored an unassisted goal from the left side at 18:30 of the first half Saturday to lift the Virginia Wesleyan men to a 1-0 ODAC soccer victory over Roanoke.
Connor Kirkham made four saves to post the shutout.
The Marlins (7-5-2, 4-3-2), who have won two in a row, are at Bridgewater on Wednesday.
